Nippon Telenet (software developer compagny)

Nippon Telenet Co. Ld. (株式会社日本テレネット) aka Telenet Japan was a Japanese video game and software developer founded in October 1983 by Kazuyuki Fukushima. It stopped its activities on 25 October 2007.

Nippon Telenet (information and communication service company)

Nippon Telenet Corporation (日本テレネット株式会社) is an compagny founded by Eijiro Taki. In March 1986, it started Japan's first image personal computer communication service "The LINKS".

It is often mentioned as Telenet Japan, but the correct name is Nippon Telenet.
